Spring REST CORS Tutorial

  This tutorial demonstrates five ways to configure Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) for
  OfficeFloor REST endpoints declared as YAML files:

   * <<Composition-level CORS>> — declared in the YAML file under <<<composition: cors:>>>, applies to
     the specific HTTP method served by that endpoint file

   * <<Annotation-level CORS>> — <<<@CrossOrigin>>> placed on the service class, picked up automatically
     by OfficeFloor at start-up

   * <<All-methods CORS>> — declared in a method-less YAML file (no HTTP method suffix), applies to
     all HTTP methods of that endpoint

   * <<Global CORS via WebMvcConfigurer>> — standard Spring <<<WebMvcConfigurer.addCorsMappings()>>>
     applies path-pattern rules across all endpoints

   * <<Global CORS via CorsConfigurationSource>> — a <<<CorsConfigurationSource>>> bean that
     OfficeFloor's handler interceptor picks up directly for OfficeFloor-managed endpoints

  {{{https://github.com/officefloor/OfficeFloor/tree/master/tutorials/springboot/SpringRestCorsHttpServer}Tutorial Source}}



